<t tx="T499">A simple literate programming language invented by Norman Ramsey.  noweb can produce derived files for any text-based programming language.

http://www.eecs.harvard.edu/~nr/noweb/</t>
<t tx="T500">The children, grandchildren, etc. of a node.</t>
<t tx="T501">An unnamed node in an @tree that contains no body text.  Such nodes may appear anywhere in an @file tree; they do not affect the derived file in any way.  In particular, organizing nodes do not affect indentation in the derived file.</t>
<t tx="T502">An unnamed node that is either 1) a descendent of a named node or 2) the descendent of no @others node.

Orphan and @ignore nodes are not allowed in @file trees: no derived file is written if an @file node contains an @ignore or orphan node.</t>
<t tx="T503">he pane containing a visual representation of outlines.</t>
